title: For Sale/Trade:  AR-15 builds and Assembly
location: West Metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Do you want a “BLACK” rifle but do not want to pay the big box prices? I can build you a custom AR-15 rifle or assemble yours for you!

Prices are as follows: (Please note that these are custom AR’s and not off the shelf toys. The COLT and USGI quality is there and reliable) Shop around and compare prices and you will see that these are reasonable! Can you beat USGI quality and reliability?

These are NEW guns and built exactly how you want.

$700 for a M4 style AR-15 (Flat top upper w/o detachable carry handle and rear sight). Upper and all internals will be USGI and the lower will be Spikes. 16" barrel. M4 stock (4 position). G.I. Handguards. Barrels are not chrome lined 4150-keeping cost down and accuracy up). Sling and magazine are not included in price. These are for the individuals that want an AR, do not want the carry handle/rear sight and want to utilize a scope and no iron sights.

$750 for a M4 style AR-15 (Flat top upper w/ carry handle and rear sight). Upper and all internals will be USGI and the lower will be Spikes. 16" barrel. M4 stock (4 position).  G.I. Handguards. Barrels are not chrome lined (4150-keeping cost down and accuracy up). Sling and magazine are not included in price. These are ideal for that modern military look with iron sights. Scope mounting can be done with proper mount.

$800 for a M16 style (AR15A2) AR-15. Upper and all internals will be USGI. Lower will be Spikes. 16" barrel. Fixed position stock. Sling and magazine are not included in price. This classic look is what our boys carried in Vietnam and has the fixed stock. No adjustability here for length of pull.

$850 for a M16 style (M16A2) AR-15. Upper and all internals will be COLT G.I. Lower will be Spikes. Sling and magazine are not included in price. Same style as above but COLT internals. 20" M16A2 full length heavy profile 5.56mm 1-9 twist barrel. Fixed position stock.

PLEASE NOTE: If you wish to have a different lower used than the above mentioned Spikes, please tell us and we can get you a price on that build!

We can also add any options you would like. Please note this in your email and a price quote will be given.

M4 style rifle is pictured first and the M16 style rifle is pictured second

Do you have an AR rifle kit and you’re not mechanically inclined or don’t want to buy tools that you won’t ever use again!? Another service we are offering is AR-15 rifle assembly. Full rifle assembly for $100! Yes, $100 – that’s roughly half of what any other location will charge you. Other assembly services are offered! Please email with a specific request and I’ll get you a price a.s.a.p!!

If you’re interested, don’t delay and send me an email with any questions you may have. Note: I cannot warranty any guns due to not knowing what conditions they are going to be used in and to what extent. I will provide a 1 week functionality warranty to which we will replace any internals that might break (not that it will happen, but parts occasionally have bad days…)

Payment options are CASH or firearm trades. Trades must be of equal value of rifle MINIMUM! 50% rifle cost due at build contract agreement. Final 50% due when rifle is complete. Customer will be called once rifle is done and given 1.5 weeks to claim rifle. If rifle is not claimed during this time, both rifle and 50% down payment will be forfeited to builder and rifle will become our property. Face to Face meeting WILL be required and MN DL and copy of Permit to Purchase or  CCW permit is REQUIRED! No sales tax. Private party sale to private party.

Basically, we want to build you the AR15 YOU want and do not want to get stuck with the bill. We all want one of these rifles but do not know what kind of quality we are getting for a “big box gun”. Sure, you can spend $1,000+ for an AR but let’s be real when I say most of us can’t/won’t pay that for a fun gun.

title: For Sale/Trade:  spartan by remington over under
postcontent:
i have a BAIKAL SPARTAN SPR 310 by Remington in 12 gauge.  it is a over / under shotgun.  this is NOT the new baikal imported by EAA.  this shotgun was designed in russia, and imported by remington in the 1990's to early 2000's.  these are sturdy tough guns that offer a lot in a small package.

i baught this shotgun from a family member so i know that it has always been kept safe clean and oiled.  this gun has also been shot very little.  myself i have only put about 100 shells through it.  as for my relative, he told me that he cleaned the gn more then he shot it.  

this gun has a beautiful stock with matching forearm.  the action is tight but smooth and has not developed the sloopy loose actions that a lot of over unders are known for.  recoil but pad is in great shape.  it has 28 inch barrels that are vent ribbed and have a bead sight.  the upper barrel is set up with a full choke tube and the bottom barrel has a modified choke tube.  the barrels are blued and the bluing is in excellent condition.  this is a single trigger gun.  the bottom barrel shoots first but a simple "bump" of the trigger will make the gun fire the top barrel first instead.  the safety engages every time the gun is broke open.  you can even set the barrels to eject the spent shells everytime you open the gun or by turning a small screw, you can turn the ejector "off".  also i have a second forearm that i picked up at a gun show for this gun too.

i had my gun smith look the gun over and asked him to rate the gun.  he told me that the gun has no problems of any kind and is in perfect working order.  in his opinion, he has rated this gun as great to excellent condition.  

i have seen a few of these on gun broker and other various websites.  these are becomming harder to find and after shooting one i can see why.  this is a great over under and has a lot of the features that much much more expensive shotguns are expected to have.

i am looking to sell or trade this gun outright becasue i just do not shoot it enough and have plenty of shotguns.

title: For Sale:  Beware But Obey The law
postcontent:
A previous post is correct that you should never give a copy of your license or ccw or fill out a FFL form to buy from an indiviual. With that said you must obey the law by making sure under NC Law that who you sell to has a ccw or a purchase permit and it should go on the bill of sale. If you don't do a bill of sale you are really putting yourself in jepoardy.

Do you really want a lost or stolen handgun used in crime traced back to you without a bill of sale as proof that it is no longer your gun? In NC even a handgun gifted to a family member must be supported by a ccw or purchase permit from the spouse, brother, sister that you give it to. 

This is the law not my opinion. Lets obey it and not give these yahoos in congress or Raleigh any reason to pass more gun control.

title: For Sale:  Colt Single Action Army, Built 1925 .45 Colt
postcontent: SN 348014 is a late smokeless single action in .45 Colt, with a 7 1/2" barrel and correct scratched numbered original grips. The barrel shows 97% bright original blue with slight holster ware; the muzzle, sight and leading edge of the ejector housing. The straps show about 95% with slight turning. The cylinder shows the obvious use on the face, edge wear on the flutes, back edge and a slight drag line. The cylinder rates at 90% plus. The case color is vivid and bright on the left side. The right shows some wear above the trigger and on the high point of the loading gate. For reference see Kopec, Chapter 16 pg. 169. The Rampant Colt on the frame shows a weak stamp which was the short arc die seen in many of Colts in the 344500 to 357869 serial range; see page 172 for the "Rampant Rocking Horse" die. This piece show inspector mark F in the hammer slot. The left trigger bow shows the assembler's number "3" and the verified proof; ref.pages 173 & 174. This piece is an excellent example of the SA's built from 1920-1928. The overall condition is 90% plus as an average. An excellent plus example for the Colt single action collector or the person that wants an above average condition single action.
